> For this reason, we propose merging the features of Egotist.art into the Superciety.com platform

With the implementation of this proposal, SUPERID will receive a dedicated tab showing all the NFTs owned by the user, and simultaneously allow anyone in possession of 500 POWER to mint images as NFTs in just a few clicks. title: This first proposal sets up our quorum
description:
We are launching our DAO on Superciety today. The best tool for securely managing an organization on Elrond Network.

*Not all holders have Discord, the voting tools are limited, and the votes are not managed by a Smart Contract.*

We can control many different things by launching our DAO Smart Contract on Superciety, like the number of NFTs needed to create and validate a proposal.

**Current settings:**
Currently, one Mr Ghost is required to create a proposal. So everyone can start a proposal right away!

Moreover, the proposal needs one Mr Ghost vote to pass. You cannot simply construct a proposal and validate it on your own.

**Needed settings:**
We must therefore define this quorum together. The minimum needed of Mr Ghost votes required to approve a proposal.

This number validates the proposal but must not be inaccessible or the proposals will fail.

**Proposal:**
The amount of approved votes for this proposal is how we would define our quorum.

If you vote to approve, you are validating this proposal, and the number of votes cast by Mr Ghost will determine the quorum.

*The votes against will not be counted in the quorum if the vote is approved.*

If the vote is not approved, we will look for alternative proposals.

**Do you support setting the quorum according to the number of votes received in approval of this proposal?**

By voting NO, you deny the proposal and the 10,000,000 will remain available to use for strengthening the $eGLD/$PLATA liquidity pair pool on Maiar Exchange and/or as funds needed for the Metabonding, when we will get to that stage.

The voting period is 3 days.

title: Phase 1 of passive income
description:
Summary

This vote is to validate the launch of the first version of our passive income, which will evolve over time.

Abstract

The first poll in Discord of Ghost Clan members revealed that passive income was the most expected feature. Members indicated that they would prefer a weekly EGLD income. They also stated that all holders should be eligible for passive income.

Motivation

Passive income is a feature that provides income to collectors without their intervention! Our organization is still in its early stages, yet we have completed a large airdrop. Many wallets have kept this gift, for which we are grateful. However, at our stage of development, paying everyone a passive income appears tricky. As a result, we propose a first version of passive income that will be monthly and available to those who own at least 5 NFTs or more. Whenever it is possible to evolve passive income so that it benefits even the smallest holders, we will consult with the community and vote. 

Specification

As shown in the Gokai Labs light paper, 100% of the organization's EGLD staking income is currently injected into EGLD staking. Now, 100% of staking revenue will be returned to holders via a passive revenue stream that is automatically paid into the holder's wallet.

Several snapshots will be taken at random throughout the month, and the income will be paid to the holder on the first of each month. At the moment, the organization generates approximately 1.1 EGLD per month. There are currently approximately 55 accounts with more than 5 NFTs, for a total of approximately 578 NFTs that are eligible for passive income. This corresponds to about 0.002 EGLD per NFT. Holders with 5 NFTs will therefore receive slightly less than 0.01 EGLD per month.

Vote

If you approve this vote, you authorize the use of staking income for passive income. The first screenshot will be completed on October 31st, and the first beneficiaries will receive their income on November 1st.

If you choose to decline the vote, the staking income will continue to be staked, and we will soon propose another version of the passive income.

title: EquiStar OG - Price Update
description:
The OG Collection has a lot of value, and we have sold it at a minimum price for too long. The EquiStar OG Collection will generate 20% royalty revenue for all the upcoming NFT sales and from the new EquiStar Collection. 
Because it generates a lot of frustration for the MINT right now because there are too many Common horses in the current collection, we have decided to cut down the number of Common Horses and increase the PRICE. 

The new price will be 1 $EGLD for each MINT but with an increased chance of getting from the rare to Legendary. We are not in any rush to SOLD OUT this collection, and we are working actively to bring to the market the Auction EquiStar Collection, which will be an ongoing mint with no fixed supply. 

We ask that you are on board with this new vision and limit the OG Collection to just 5k NFTs.

This will increase the long-term revenue for the current holder. The remaining NFTs will be burned.

title: Move 303M LKMEX back into the Giants Reserve
description:
With this proposal, we aim to decide what will happen with the 303.000.000 LKMEX we had been staking in the MEX farm on xExchange(Maiar Exchange). As you probably know, LKMEX is now non-transferable, so we can‚Äôt distribute it anymore as reward.

After discussions on discord & telegram with the community, the proposal is to put the 303M LKMEX back into the Giants Reserve to be invested in developing the Giants Game and the Giants ecosystem.

A little more context for the proposal

Both the Giants team and the community members that provided feedback on discord/telegram think that rewards for a 10K collection are usually pretty small (or you need to invest a considerable amount of money to be able to give significant rewards and keep up with the APR going down). At this step, that doesn't make so much sense for the project, considering that the purpose of the project is to build the game (and all other building blocks or projects in the Giants ecosystem). Also, by giving rewards in a specific token, you make an investment into that token that can go well or not.

When the lock period for the LKMEX expires, we‚Äôll do another DAO vote to decide what will actually happen to all that LKMEX.
